     treat all pathspecs literally, rather than as glob patterns.  For
     example, running ‘GIT_LITERAL_PATHSPECS=1 git log -- '*.c'’ will
     search for commits that touch the path ‘*.c’, not any paths that
     the glob ‘*.c’ matches.  You might want this if you are feeding
     literal paths to Git (e.g., paths previously given to you by ‘git
     ls-tree’, ‘--raw’ diff output, etc).

