     or badly named refs when iterating over lists of refs.  Normally
     Git will try to include any such refs, which may cause some
     operations to fail.  This is usually preferable, as potentially
     destructive operations (e.g., git-prune(1)) are better off aborting
     rather than ignoring broken refs (and thus considering the history
     they point to as not worth saving).  The default value is ‘1’
